Data analysis is an essential part of the research process. It involves collecting, organizing, analyzing, and interpreting data to draw conclusions and make informed decisions. Data analysis can be performed in various ways, depending on the type of data and the research objective. Some common techniques include descriptive analysis, inferential analysis, and predictive analysis. Descriptive analysis involves presenting data in a clear and concise manner, while inferential analysis seeks to identify patterns and relationships among the data. Predictive analysis, on the other hand, uses statistical models to forecast future outcomes based on existing data.
